This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with facial expression recognition, which is a common task in computer vision. The use of neural networks and deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of understanding human cognitive states, which could place it in the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the use of visual representations and datasets related to facial expressions could also suggest that it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
